The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Curry love
                                                                                                               Curry love
                            
	London, Aug. 17 (PTI): A Bangladeshi cricketer has spent 4,000 to fly in food and cooks from his favourite Indian curry house in Britain to Dubai.        
	Test player Habibul Bashar shelled out the money to fly chefs from Amish Indian Restaurant in Chobham to cook for his 37th birthday party today in Dubai.              
	 British tabloid The Sun reported. The batsman loved their chicken, lamb and vegetable dishes when he was in England for the World Twenty20 Cup this summer. His bumper birthday order  including flights  has cost 4,270 pounds, the report said. He took our card and said hed be in touch. Its nice he thought that much of our food, the restaurant manager Amin Ali was quoted as saying. PTI MOT MOT 08171635 DELHI NNNN                                                                                                                                                                           
